Hatteras Funds Announces New Sales and Marketing Directors | Business Wire


























































Hatteras Funds Announces New Sales and Marketing Directors






May 04, 2010 11:35 AM Eastern Daylight Time



RALEIGH, N.C.--(BUSINESS WIRE)--Hatteras Funds, a leading provider of unique alternative investment 
      solutions specifically designed for financial professionals, is pleased 
      to announce today four new appointments to its sales and marketing teams.
    


      Caron R. Brown has joined Hatteras as Director of National Accounts. She 
      assumes the role from Robert B. Brown, who has been promoted to the 
      position of Director of Marketing. Ms. Brown and Mr. Brown are not 
      related. Joseph T. McMenamin has also joined the Hatteras team as 
      Regional Director for the Northeast territory, and John W. Vaughan has 
      joined the team as Regional Director for the recently created New 
      England territory.
    

      “Caron, Rob, John and Joe are experienced professionals with deep 
      insights to the advisor community, and we expect that they will 
      significantly expand Hatteras’ presence. They will play an important 
      part in bringing the Hatteras Funds offering and value-added services to 
      substantially more advisors and their clients,” said Chief Executive 
      Officer Brian Jacobs. “They have each been through different market 
      cycles that have created demands for new investment solutions. They each 
      understand the importance of alternatives in post-recession portfolios 
      and how they are integrated with traditional investments.”
    

      “These professionals bring significant experience to Hatteras, further 
      reinforcing our ongoing commitment to our client, the financial 
      professional,” said Founder and Chairman David B. Perkins.
    

      Ms. Brown has over 15 years of financial services experience. She joins 
      Hatteras from J.P. Morgan Asset Management, where she was Vice President 
      and Senior Relationship manager responsible for increasing distribution 
      to the independent broker/dealer and bank channels. Before joining J.P. 
      Morgan in 2006, Ms. Brown spent three years as Vice President, 
      Relationship Management, at Merrill Lynch Investment Managers.
    

      Mr. Brown joined Hatteras in 2004 and has more than a decade of 
      alternative investment industry experience. Before joining the firm, he 
      was Vice President of Alternative Strategies at Highland Associates, 
      where he held a range of responsibilities that included alternative 
      investment strategy research, manager search and due diligence 
      functions, as well as client education. Mr. Brown will continue his 
      responsibility as liaison for the RIA space as well as a strong focus on 
      enhancing education and marketing materials for financial professionals.
    

      With over 16 years of financial services experience, Mr. McMenamin joins 
      Hatteras Funds from Allianz Global Investors, where he was Senior Vice 
      President and Divisional Sales Manager for the East Coast Region from 
      2007-2010, and Vice President from 2001-2007. Among his responsibilities 
      at Allianz Global Investors were the development of business 
      relationships and top-down support for advisors within banks, 
      independent, regional and wirehouse firms. Previously, he spent eight 
      successful years with Eaton Vance Distributors, most recently as 
      Regional Vice President.
    

      Joining Hatteras as Regional Director for New England, John W. Vaughan 
      brings over 25 years of financial services experience to the firm. 
      Before joining Hatteras, Mr. Vaughan was Vice President and Regional 
      Director in the Wealth Management Solutions Group at Eaton Vance, a 
      position he had held since 2007. In this capacity, he was responsible 
      for the sale and service of Eaton Vance’s high-net-worth offerings. In 
      2007, he was appointed a Director of Eaton Vance’s Wealth Management 
      Solutions Group. From 2001 to 2007, he was Managing Director of 
      Alternative Investments, responsible for the development and sales of 
      the firm’s private placements and charitable gift trust products. He 
      joined Eaton Vance in 1999. Earlier Mr. Vaughan served as an enforcement 
      attorney with the Massachusetts Securities Division and as a state 
      prosecutor. From 1985 to 1991, he was a financial consultant and 
      brokerage manager at Fidelity Investments. He holds the J.D. from the 
      New England School of Law, and the Chartered Private Wealth Advisor (CPWASM) 
      designation.
    

      Biographies of each executive can be found at: Hatteras 
      Funds -- Our Team


